Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "heroja" (*hero*) in different forms and positions, along with their English translations in parentheses:

1. *Heroja* sam upoznao juče. (I met a *hero* yesterday.)
2. Molim te, pozajmi mi knjigu o *herojima*. (Please lend me a book about *heroes*.)
3. On je bio *heroj* u ratu. (He was a *hero* in the war.)
4. Njegova hrabrost ga čini *herojem*. (His bravery makes him a *hero*.)
5. On je pravi *heroj* za svoju porodicu. (He is a true *hero* for his family.)
6. Svi su *heroji* na svoj način. (Everyone is a *hero* in their own way.)
7. Ovaj film govori o *herojstvu*. (This movie is about *heroism*.)
8. Nema *heroja* bez hrabrosti. (There are no *heroes* without courage.)
9. *Heroji* su slavni zbog svojih podviga. (*Heroes* are famous for their deeds.)
10. *Herojstvo* nije samo za vojnike. (*Heroism* is not just for soldiers.)

Note: The word "heroja" can have different meanings depending on the context, but in these sentences, it generally refers to a heroic person or quality.